reviews.title: Works great on Galaxy S2 with headphones
reviews.comment: I\'ve tried pretty much all SIP/VoIP clients on Android. CSipSimple is among the best in terms of functionality and integration, but it has problems with the headphone mic sensitivity (too low). Even after tweaking the CSipSimple settings mic gain/volume is not acceptable on my Galaxy S2. Keyyo is based on CSipSimple, but seem to be improved in multiple ways. The mic sensitivity can be reliably increased to a point where the volume is now adequate. Also, the user interface is a bit cleaner than CSipSimple. Dialer integration works just as well as CSipSimple. Overall, this is the most reliable, best integrated SIP/VoIP client and the only one where headphone mic gain works reliably. Thanks!
